2026-02-03T18:31:59.2470272Z Note: a multi-user installation is possible. See https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/installation/installing-binary.html#multi-user-installation
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2480724Z [1;31mSwitching to the Multi-user Installer[0m
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2573813Z [32mWelcome to the Multi-User Nix Installation
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2583279Z [0m
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2583623Z This installation tool will set up your computer with the Nix package
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2584008Z manager. This will happen in a few stages:
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2584201Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2584354Z 1. Make sure your computer doesn't already have Nix. If it does, I
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2585019Z    will show you instructions on how to clean up your old install.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2585405Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2585652Z 2. Show you what I am going to install and where. Then I will ask
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2586152Z    if you are ready to continue.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2586314Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2586670Z 3. Create the system users [34m(uids [30001..30008])[0m and groups [34m(gid 30000)[0m
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2587439Z    that the Nix daemon uses to run builds. To create system users
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2588079Z    in a different range, exit and run this tool again with
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2588584Z    NIX_FIRST_BUILD_UID set.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2588813Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589045Z 4. Perform the basic installation of the Nix files daemon.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589278Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589439Z 5. Configure your shell to import special Nix Profile files, so you
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589753Z    can use Nix.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589860Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2589932Z 6. Start the Nix daemon.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2590079Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2590425Z [32m[4;32mWould you like to see a more detailed list of what I will do?
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2590839Z [0mNo TTY, assuming you would say yes :)
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2597511Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2597810Z I will:
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2598011Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2598263Z  - make sure your computer doesn't already have Nix files
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2598767Z    (if it does, I will tell you how to clean them up.)
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2599144Z  - create local users (see the list above for the users I'll make)
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2599483Z  - create a local group (nixbld)
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2599708Z  - install Nix in /nix
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2599922Z  - create a configuration file in /etc/nix
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2600255Z  - set up the "default profile" by creating some Nix-related files in
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2601252Z    /root
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2613594Z  - back up /etc/bash.bashrc to /etc/bash.bashrc.backup-before-nix
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2624685Z  - update /etc/bash.bashrc to include some Nix configuration
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2625432Z  - load and start a service (at /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.service
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2626158Z    and /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.socket) for nix-daemon
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2626565Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2626849Z [32m[4;32mReady to continue?
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2627862Z [0mNo TTY, assuming you would say yes :)
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2645170Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2646732Z [34m---- let's talk about sudo -----------------------------------------------------
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2655970Z [0mThis script is going to call sudo a lot. Normally, it would show you
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2656764Z exactly what commands it is running and why. However, the script is
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2657382Z run in a headless fashion, like this:
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2657678Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2657869Z   $ curl -L https://nixos.org/nix/install | sh
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2658205Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2658474Z or maybe in a CI pipeline. Because of that, I'm going to skip the
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2659190Z verbose output in the interest of brevity.
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2659861Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2659994Z If you would like to
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2660355Z see the output, try like this:
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2660616Z 
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2660864Z   $ curl -L -o install-nix https://nixos.org/nix/install
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2661379Z   $ sh ./install-nix
2026-02-03T18:31:59.2661585Z 
